      "content": "While your concern is understandable, skipping a dose of basal insulin without medical guidance is still a risk. Basal insulin covers your body's baseline needs, not just the immediate effects of a meal. If you are very concerned, you could try checking your blood sugar a few hours after your usual bedtime as a safety measure. However, for a definitive plan, waiting until Monday to speak with a healthcare professional is the safest course of action.",
      "source": "target",
